oc:kn_0445e93b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before referencing these templates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Phase 4 of the create-cowork-plugin workflow must be reached before using these examples for implementation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These examples are implementation templates used after planning phases are complete." .

oc:kn_88826a74 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — this is the minimal required plugin configuration" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every plugin must contain .claude-plugin/plugin.json with name, version, description, and author fields at minimum." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without plugin.json, the plugin cannot be discovered or loaded by the runtime." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_89b13e0c a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any SKILL.md file" ;
    oc:directiveContent "SKILL.md frontmatter must include name and description with trigger phrases in the description using the pattern: Use when the user asks to \"trigger phrase 1\", \"trigger phrase 2\", or \"trigger phrase 3\"." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Trigger phrases in descriptions enable the agent to match user requests to the correct skill automatically." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_8ac817ce a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building plugins for team workflows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Full-featured plugins should include SessionStart hooks that inject team context (sprint cycle, standup schedule, tool references) as echo commands." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Session context injection ensures the agent always has current team process information without explicit user prompting." .

oc:kn_9464b19f a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When plugin skills reference external tools or services" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not hardcode specific tool names in plugin skill files. Use tool-agnostic placeholders like ~~category (e.g., ~~project tracker) and document mappings in CONNECTORS.md." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Tool-agnostic connectors allow plugins to work across different tool ecosystems without modification." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c1aeff61 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning a new plugin's structure" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Plugins exist at three complexity tiers: Minimal (single skill), Standard (skills + MCP), and Full-Featured (skills + agents + hooks + MCP + connectors). Choose the tier that matches the plugin's scope." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Starting with the right complexity tier avoids over-engineering simple plugins and under-equipping complex ones." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

